Time to do feedback with your pair programming partner

Here are the feedback guidelines for your reference:

1) Start with a self-reflection time for both in the pair. Explain to your partner:
- I think I did this well (ex.: I diagrammed and whiteboarded each problem in a very detailed manner)
- I think I could improve (ex.: I might have bulldozed a bit and should have considered your approach instead of forcing my own)
--> These should involve reflection on time spent in both rolls
- Where do I think I fell 1-10 on the not contributing (1) to bulldozing (10) scale?

2) Evaluate each other:
- I think you did this well (ex.: You asked me really good probing questions instead of giving me the answer)
- I think you could improve on this (ex.: Though it takes a little longer, we should focus on slowing down and completing challenges so that we understand them, not so we can finish them)
--> These should involve reflection on time spent in both rolls
- I agree/disagree on where you placed yourself on the scale, and why
- I think you could have done _____ to make the learning experience better. [press them to find something to help them grow. (ex.: you should check your phone less, I feel like you ask the same question multiple times without truly trying to understand)]
- I learned _____ from pair programming with you (ex.: during pairing I see more and more how important it is to let the navigator guide all the way through, even if I think it is the wrong approach)
- How did we feel about our code review and our refactoring on this unit / what we produced?
